Let $${f_1}:R \to R,\,{f_2}:\left( { - {\pi  \over 2},{\pi  \over 2}} \right) \to R,\,{f_3}:( - 1,{e^{\pi /2}} - 2) \to R$$ and $${f_4}:R \to R$$ be functions defined by<br><br>(i) $${f_1}(x) = \sin (\sqrt {1 - {e^{ - {x^2}}}} )$$,<br><br>(ii) $${f_2}(x) = \left\{ \matrix{
  {{|\sin x|} \over {\tan { - ^1}x}}if\,x \ne 0,\,where \hfill \cr 
  1\,if\,x = 0 \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br><br>the inverse trigonometric function tan<sup>$$-$$1</sup>x assumes values in $$\left( { - {\pi  \over 2},{\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$,<br><br>(iii) $${f_3}(x) = [\sin ({\log _e}(x + 2))]$$, where for $$t \in R,\,[t]$$ denotes the greatest integer less than or equal to t,<br><br>(iv) $${f_4}(x) = \left\{ \matrix{
  {x^2}\sin \left( {{1 \over x}} \right)\,if\,x \ne 0 \hfill \cr 
  0\,if\,x = 0 \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br>
<style>
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        th {
            background-color: blue;
            color: white;
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 10px;
        }
